dct_title_s: Map of part of British New Guinea
dct_description_sm: Drawn by W. R. Cuthbertson ; Lithographed at the Department of Lands and Survey Melbourne by T. Slater.
Relief shown by shading and spot heights (at peaks).
Insets: Mount Obree, Owen Stanley Range B.N.C.; Mount Owen Stanley.

Topographical text, such as "Well grassed bald hills," "limestone," "wild sugar cane," and "Apparently succession of Ranges in this direction but owing to the very wet wet [sic] and misty weather experienced throughout the trip was unable to correctly define character of country."
Shows drainage, villages, various place names.
dct_creator_sm: Victoria, Department of Crown Lands and Survey.
